.TH "NAVIGATIONDESTINATION" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
NavigationDestination \- NavigationDestination
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]NavigationDestination\f[B]\f[R] interface of the
Navigation API represents the destination being navigated to in the
current navigation.
.PP
It is accessed via the \f[CR]NavigateEvent.destination\f[R] property.
.SH INSTANCE PROPERTIES
.TP
\f[B]id\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
Returns the \f[CR]id\f[R] value of the destination
\f[CR]NavigationHistoryEntry\f[R] if the
\f[CR]NavigateEvent.navigationType\f[R] is \f[CR]traverse\f[R], or an
empty string otherwise.
.TP
\f[B]index\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
Returns the \f[CR]index\f[R] value of the destination
\f[CR]NavigationHistoryEntry\f[R] if the
\f[CR]NavigateEvent.navigationType\f[R] is \f[CR]traverse\f[R], or
\f[CR]\-1\f[R] otherwise.
.TP
\f[B]key\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
Returns the \f[CR]key\f[R] value of the destination
\f[CR]NavigationHistoryEntry\f[R] if the
\f[CR]NavigateEvent.navigationType\f[R] is \f[CR]traverse\f[R], or an
empty string otherwise.
.TP
\f[B]sameDocument\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
Returns \f[CR]true\f[R] if the navigation is to the same
\f[CR]document\f[R] as the current \f[CR]Document\f[R] value, or
\f[CR]false\f[R] otherwise.
.TP
\f[B]url\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
Returns the URL being navigated to.
.SH INSTANCE METHODS
.TP
\f[B]getState()\f[R]
Returns a clone of the available state associated with the destination
\f[CR]NavigationHistoryEntry\f[R], or navigation operation (e.g.,
\f[CR]navigate()\f[R]) as appropriate.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
navigation.addEventListener(\(dqnavigate\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  \f[I]// Exit early if this navigation shouldn\(aqt be intercepted,\f[R]
  \f[I]// e.g. if the navigation is cross\-origin, or a download request\f[R]
  \f[B]if\f[R] (shouldNotIntercept(event)) {
    \f[B]return\f[R];
  }

  \f[I]// Returns a URL() object constructed from the\f[R]
  \f[I]// NavigationDestination.url value\f[R]
  \f[B]const\f[R] url = \f[B]new\f[R] URL(event.destination.url);

  \f[B]if\f[R] (url.pathname.startsWith(\(dq/articles/\(dq)) {
    event.intercept({
      \f[B]async\f[R] handler() {
        \f[I]// The URL has already changed, so show a placeholder while\f[R]
        \f[I]// fetching the new content, such as a spinner or loading page\f[R]
        renderArticlePagePlaceholder();

        \f[I]// Fetch the new content and display when ready\f[R]
        \f[B]const\f[R] articleContent = \f[B]await\f[R] getArticleContent(url.pathname);
        renderArticlePage(articleContent);
      },
    });
  }
});
.EE
